summary: One day she came back [...] her hair all tangled and her clothes covered in mud, clutching a raggedy bunch of purple and green...
body:
One day she came back […] her hair all tangled and her clothes covered in mud, clutching a raggedy bunch of purple and green flowers for Father. Sansa kept hoping he would tell Arya to behave herself and act like the highborn lady she was supposed to be, but he never did, he only hugged her and thanked her for the flowers.

the journey south is a tedious, unfun experience for sansa but arya eagerly explores the land. she’s curious about the nature and picks some flowers for ned. sansa describes them as “raggedy” and looks down on arya for picking them but ned is thankful and he hugs arya. the act was a sincere gesture of love from arya to her father. like arya the flowers are untamed and dangerous with a beauty not all might be able to appreciate. but they are in their wild and natural glory. arya is also associated with oak trees which are symbols of the forest that represent strength

To the other maidens he had given white roses, but the one he plucked for her was red. “Sweet lady,” he said, “no victory is half so beautiful as you.” Sansa took the flower timidly, struck dumb by his gallantry. […] She inhaled the sweet fragrance of the rose and sat clutching it long after Ser Loras had ridden off.

arya refuses to attend but the tourney in kings landing is a magical event for sansa. she’s given a flower by a knight. red roses are the most classic representation from the plant world of love and desire. to receive this flower from loras means “everything” to sansa. but its a hollow gesture typical of court life from loras. he doesnt love sansa, forgets even giving her the rose and is attracted to men. much like sansa this sweet smelling flower has been cultivated in a garden to appeal to mankind’s aesthetic sensibilities. she’s also been associated with jonquils which are prized by society too

summary: What do you think is Arya's endgame? She gets a significant amount of pagetime, but unlike say Jon, Bran or Sansa I find it...
question: What do you think is Arya's endgame? She gets a significant amount of pagetime, but unlike say Jon, Bran or Sansa I find it really hard to gauge where her arc is going. What use is an assassin in the war against the Others (and she seems headed away from the revenge path anyway)? Heading Nynerias Wolfpack seems too obvious and renders her training as a faceless woman superflous. I'd love to hear your thoughts.
answer:
I’m not sure what Arya will end up doing exactly (especially during the new War for the Dawn), but I’m pretty sure of how she’ll fit into the springtime Starkling dynamic. 

Bran’s strengths are magical - what he’ll accomplish in his lifetime will help people for centuries, if not millennia. Sansa’s strengths are political - what she’ll accomplish will improve lives over years and decades. Arya’s strengths, though, they’re the strengths best suited to making a difference in the moment. Arya will be the Stark to go to for quick, effective fact-finding and justice on the spot.

summary: Thirty yards from shore, three black swans were gliding over the water, so serene … no one had told them that war had come, and...
text: Thirty yards from shore, three black swans were gliding over the water, so serene … no one had told them that war had come, and they cared nothing for burning towns and butchered men. She stared at them with yearning. Part of her wanted to be a swan. The other part wanted to eat one.
source: Arya Stark, A Clash of Kings

summary: as promised, here are some photos of our cosplays from the weekend - featuring sansa, margaery, and arya!  we all got stopped so...
caption:
as promised, here are some photos of our cosplays from the weekend - featuring sansa, margaery, and arya! 

we all got stopped so many times for photos and compliments (there was even a guy who could barely speak because of a sore throat but made sure to come over and say how much he loved our costumes - honestly, what a sweetheart!) there weren’t many game of thrones cosplays so people appreciated our efforts! i would walk down the corridors and here people say variations of: “that’s sansa stark!”, “she’s the lady of winterfell!”, “lady stark (bows)”, “my queen!” and i wanted to die of happiness!

also thoughts and feelings: should i upload the last picture and tag sophie on twitter in the hopes the feeling is mutual when it comes to “leaks” of sansa’s death in s8??
